Kenya Kwanza presidential candidate William Ruto will on Monday take his campaigns to Meru county. He will be accompanied by his running mate Rigathi Gachagua. They will start off the campaigns at Kaguma, then proceed to Kithirune in Central Imenti Constituency. They will later go to Chuguu, North Imenti Constituency and Sunbird Stage. The campaign trail will end at Tutua, and Gìtimene in Bùùrì Constituency. The DP started his Meru campaign on Sunday. Azimio flagbearer Raila Odinga will on the other hand, hold an open diary in Nairobi. Raila had on Sunday taken his campaigns in Homa Bay county. His running mate Martha Karua will also take the Azimio gospel to Njoro, in Nakuru county. She will be received by Nakuru Governor Lee Kinyanjui. Karua will start off the campaigns from Tipis, and proceed to Mwisho wa Lami, Mau Narok, Likia, Mauche, Stoo Mbili, and finally finish at Naishi. Karua on Sunday held her campaigns in Nairobi.